node.text:
By @grillhunters 
.
Have you ever had a grilled romaine salad before? If not, you’re in for a unique and delicious smoky surprise.

Here’s a list of ingredients for the marinade and salad. Full recipe with instruction is on the blog.

// Garlic & herbs marinade //
- 3/4 cup olive oil
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tbsp basil, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp chives, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp rosemary, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp parsley, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp lemon zest
- 3 garlic cloves, minced
- 1/2 tsp chili powder
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp black pepper

// Grilles Romaine Salad //
- 1 heart romaine lettuce cut in half lengthwise 
- ½ cup Parmesan cheese flakes
- 4 slice bacon grilled and crispy
- 4 tbsp olive oil extra virgin
- 1 tbsp kosher salt
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tsp back pepper
- ½ lemon zest

#NomadGrills #grillhunters #grilledlettuce #grilledsalad #vealchop #grilledvealchops #smokedveal

node.text:
Four Healthy MealPrep Breakfast Ideas for this week!! 🍳🥞🧀 Meal prep is so worth it, all week long you can enjoy a variety of breakfasts and your freezer is stocked with extras!
Swipe left to see ..
✅Classic Banana Pancakes
✅Blueberry Oat Cups
✅Veggie Frittata
✅Egg Quesadillas
⠀
⠀
👉🏼🤷🏻‍♀️When I don’t prep breakfasts, I end up eating cereal, toast or oatmeal. There’s nothing wrong with those but I was getting bored. 💯Meal prep to the rescue! I just don’t want to spend 30 minutes preparing, cooking breakfast and cleaning dishes every day. I’d rather sleep in tbh 😇 Hope this inspires you to switch up your breakfast routine if you’re in a rut! Thanks to @workweeklunch for these recipes x

node.text:
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness for the best nutrition, mindset and fitness tips
.
What bowl 🥣 is your go to!?? 1️⃣↔️6️⃣ comment below and let me know!👇 
All these by @daliciousdish 
-
1️⃣BURGER BOWL🍔 
.
.
Loaded burger bowls! A bowl of all the goods!
.
.
80/20 ground Chuck 
Colbey Jack cheese 
Bread & butter pickles 
sweet potato fries 
Avocado 
Grape tomatoes 
Red onions 
.
. 
#dEATS Burger patties seasoned with sea salt and pepper. Air-fry the sweet potato fries at 400 degrees for 15 mins.Hope everyone is having a wonderful day!

2️⃣ Shrimp bowl 🦐 
.
.
A bowl of all the goods! I had some lettuce I needed to use and decided to make a loaded salad bowl!
.
.
Pan seared jumbo shrimp
Black beans 
Grape tomatoes
Corn
double roasted salsa for dressing
.
. 
#dEATS Shrimp seasoned with garlic powder, smoked paprika, sea salt and pepper. On medium heat, sear each side for 2-3 mins with avocado oil. 
.
3️⃣turmeric falafel 
Campari tomatoes
Cucumbers
Feta cheese
Kalamata olives 
.
.
4️⃣Chicken Cobb🥗 
.
.
Nothing like a classic salad for dinner tonight! 
.
.
Grilled chicken breast 
Spring mix
Grape tomatoes
Avocado 
Red onions 
Blue cheese crumbles 
boiled eggs
.
.
#dEATS Grilled chicken breast seasoned with garlic powder, smoked paprika, S&P. You can bake at 375 for 42-45 mins. For dressing, I used regular balsamic vinegar!

5️⃣Blue Cheese Steak
.
.
We all know that avocado & toast pairs perfect, but man does steak & blue cheese pairs perfectly, too 😍
.
.
6oz filet
Spring mix
Campari tomatoes
Red onions
Avocado
Blue cheese 
Balsamic vinegar for dressing 
.
.
#dEATS Grilled 6oz filet seasoned with lemon pepper, sea salt, & fresh cracked pepper! 

6️⃣SALSA VERDE CHICKEN BOWL 
.
.
It’s definitely an easy crockpot meal day! 
.
.
3 chicken breasts
2 Salsa Verde jars
Lettuce
Brown rice
Black beans
Grape tomatoes
Limes
.
.
#dEATS I put 3 chicken breast in my crockpot seasoned with sea salt and pepper. Then poured 2 salsa verde jars on top and cook at low heat for 6-7 hours. Shredded with two forks and it’s ready to go!

#deliciousdish #healthyliving #balancedlifestyle #healthy #healthybowl #bowl #bowls

node.text:
Sweet & spicy pan fried salmon 🤤

Who’s down to try this recipe by @thatfoodiejess 

for oven version: 
* in a baking dish, put a large sheet of foil and add marinated salmon pieces and marinade
* fold ends of foil sheet to form a parcel (basically enclosing the salmon in the foil)
* bake at 190° for 10-15 (depends on thickness, for this size I usually do 12 mins)
* open up parcel to expose the top of salmon, then continue to bake for 5 minutes or until top is slightly brown. 

ingredients:

• 2 salmon slices 
• 1 tbsp oyster sauce 
• 1 1/2 tbsp light soy sauce 
• 1 tbsp brown sugar 
• 1 tsp garlic ginger paste 
• 1 tbsp water 
• 1/2 tsp chilli flakes (adjust to liking) 
• 1/2 tsp sesame oil 
• less than handful chopped coriander/cilantro 

method: 
1. mix sauce ingredients ingredients 
2. marinate salmon for at least 15 mins, best is 30 mins
3. Pan fry for total 10-12 mins, browning all sides, around 2 minutes each side then when all brown, cook remaining time with skin side down. (hope this makes sense 😅) 
4. when salmon almost done, add in marinade and coat salmon.
5. serve over rice, noodles, salad or anythinggg
